info: ~4 billion years ago. The Preservers are the first of the humanoid races to explore the galaxy. They receive a genetically encoded hologram from Captain Jean-Luc Picard, sent through a wormhole from four billion years in the future.

note: The time and place of Borg origins is speculative and hotly debated. Placement here is based primarily upon Peter David's assertion in Vendetta that the Borg fought a war with the Preservers.
info: ~4 billion years ago. A disasterous experiment with medical nanotechnology by an unknown race results in the creation of the Borg.
~64 million years ago. The Enterprise crew witnesses the asteroid collision with prehistoric Earth, causing the extinction of the dinosaurs.
~27800 BC. Backstory
source: Horn And Ivory - Gateways: What Lay Beyond

info: ~2700 BC. Birth of Spock's son on Sarpeidon.
~300 BC. Early Vulcan space travel (a.k.a. The Age Of Expansion).
Birth of Surak, son of T'Leia and Stef, on Vulcan.

note: As seen by Picard within a vision, this may be historically unreliable. In Spock's World, both of Surak's parents remain alive well into his adulthood.
info: ~70 BC. Stef is critically wounded in a battle on the Ishaya plain. Prior to his death, he gives the Ko N'ya stone to Surak, who in turn gives it to the warrior Garamond.
Surak discovers his calling in a vision at Mount Seleya.
Vulcans make first contact with the Orions, resulting in the bloodiest war of Vulcan's history. S'task, a student of Surak's, is captured and leads a violent uprising to escape.
source: Rihannsu 2: The Romulan Way - TOS 35; Spock's World - Vulcan Six

info: Death of Zakal the Terrible, a Kolinahr master, on Vulcan. Nortakh continues the fight of the Kolinahru against Surak's teachings.
Rejecting Surak's reforms, S'task and eighty thousand followers leave Vulcan in search of a new world.
source: Rihannsu 2: The Romulan Way - TOS 35 Ch 2, 4

info: Surak is assassinated by Yhri terrorists.
~500. The Vulcan Travelers, known as the Rihannsu, make planetfall on the twin worlds of ch'Rihan and ch'Havran.
source: Rihannsu 2: The Romulan Way - TOS 35 Ch 6

info: ~500. The Adepts of T'Pel settle upon the East Continent of ch'Havran.
~578. The rise of the Ruling Queen among the Rihannsu.
source: Rihannsu 2: The Romulan Way - TOS 35 Ch 8

info: ~830-870. The Heroic Age on Qo'noS.
~1570. The Supreme Ruler of Jibet and a thousand followers leave the planet in the sleeper ship Nibix.
Via the Guardian of Forever, Uhura arrives in Earth's past to retrieve William Harrod. She has a short affair with William Shakespeare.
Hikaru Sulu, a.k.a. Okiri Heihachiro, serves as a bodyguard for Lord Torii Mototada in feudal Japan.
Montgomery Scott marches in the Great Scottish Rebellion.
October 11. Commanded by Captain Israel Daniel Dickenson, the sloop-of-war Enterprise and the American rebel fleet on Lake Champlain repel the British Royal Navy at Valcour Island.
source: The Veil At Valcour - The Enterprise Logs

info: Colonel Thaddius Riker dies on the field of battle during the American Civil War.
source: A Q To Swear By - SNW 3

info: Spock arrives on Earth from the future to prevent the Klingons from altering history.
~1873. On Zondar, the prophet Ontear leaves his writings to his student, Suti.
July 21. Arizona ranger John Dawson discovers an ancient transporter within a Hopi ruin in southwest Colorado. He leaves behind his Colt .45 Peacemakers on the planet Equinox.
June 19. John Dawson returns to southwest Colorado but is unable to locate his Colt .45s.
A homeless man known as Rodent accidentally disintegrates himself with a phaser.
Edith Keeler is struck by an automobile and killed, preventing her founding of a peace movement that would have resulted in a victory for the Axis powers in World War 2.
source: The City On The Edge Of Forever - Star Trek 2; Triptych - SNW 2

note: It is unlikely that this is the same Benny Russell who worked for the magazine Incredible Tales Of Scientific Wonder since he would only be fourteen, did not write for radio, and did not yet have knowledge of the Bajoran orb.
info: October 28. A science-fiction radio play written by Ben Russell is broadcast.
source: Captain Proton And The Orb Of Bajor - SNW 4

note: It would appear that in Benny Russell's reality, Star Trek is his own fictional creation. This reality is experienced in a vision by Captain Sisko.
info: July. 16 year-old Benny Russell attends the annual fair at Flushing Meadow, where he views a strange orb allegedly of extraterrestrial origin.
October 26. The aircraft carrier USS Enterprise, under command of Captain Osborne B. Hardison, supports Task Force 16 against Japanese attacks at Guadalcanal during World War 2.
October 26. Pavel Alexandrovitch Chuikov is awarded Hero Of The Soviet Union, First Class, in World War 2.
December 5. Naval lieutenant Charles Taylor leads a squadron of Avenger torpedo bombers on a training mission into the Bermuda Triangle. All five planes vanish into a spatial anomaly.
October. Science fiction writer Benny Russell pens the story of an alien space station called Deep Space Nine. However, due to issues of racism, the story will not be published.
December 14. Benny Russell is institutionalized and is treated by Dr. James Wykoff. He will be released in four months after completing his Deep Space Nine serial story.

Actors William Shatner, Leonard Nimoy and DeForest Kelley are temporarily transported into a fictional universe while filming an episode of the Star Trek television series (probably 'The Omega Glory').
source: Visit To A Weird Planet Revisited - The New Voyages

info: April 4. Dr. Martin Luther King Jr. is assassinated. Dr. Wykoff reflects upon Benny Russell's hopes for the future of race relations.
April 4. Gary Seven prevents the detonation of an orbital atomic weapon by the United States.
July. The Enterprise abducts U.S. Air Force Captain John Christopher, but is forced to return him to prevent the altering of Earth's history.
July. Jimmy Wainwright attempts to coerce Christopher into leaking his report of a UFO sighting to the press. Roberta Lincoln, companion to Gary Seven, intercedes.
July. Gary Seven, in his office, discovers that the Romulans have altered future events.

May. Gary Seven, along with Roberta Lincoln and Isis, infiltrate and destroy the underground base of the Chrysalis Project in Rajasthan, India. Dozens of genetically engineered children are rescued, including four year-old Khan Noonien Singh, the son of the project director Sarina Kaur.
source: The Eugenics Wars: The Rise And Fall Of Khan Noonien Singh Vol 1 Ch 1-23

info: November 1. Gary Seven rescues Khan from the rioting in Delhi following the assassination of Indira Gandhi.
source: The Eugenics Wars: The Rise And Fall Of Khan Noonien Singh Vol 1 Ch 26-27

info: December 2. Khan accompanies Gary Seven to Antarctica to confront atmospheric researcher Dr. Wilson Evergreen, who is discovered to be immortal when Khan stabs him.
source: The Eugenics Wars: The Rise And Fall Of Khan Noonien Singh Vol 1 Ch 29-30

info: The Enterprise retrieves two humpback whales for the purpose of communicating with an alien probe.
Detective Chizum investigates the unexplained disappearance of Dr. Gillian Taylor.
July 5. Roberta Lincoln retrieves Chekov's phaser and communicator from Area 51 in Nevada.
source: The Eugenics Wars: The Rise And Fall Of Khan Noonien Singh Vol 1 Ch 31

info: October 10. Seven and Lincoln succeed in foiling an assassination attempt upon Mikhail Gorbachev. Khan arrives to assist Seven, thus repaying his life debt.
source: The Eugenics Wars: The Rise And Fall Of Khan Noonien Singh Vol 1 Ch 32-33

info: November 9. Khan invades Seven's office to obtain information regarding the whereabouts of the other children from the Chrysalis Project.
source: The Eugenics Wars: The Rise And Fall Of Khan Noonien Singh Vol 1 Ch 34

info: NA
source: The Man Who Sold The Sky - SNW 1

info: June 14. Roberta Lincoln fails in her attempt to prevent Khan from launching his Morning Star satellite, capable of selectively destroying portions of the Earth's ozone layer.
source: The Eugenics Wars: The Rise And Fall Of Khan Noonien Singh Vol 2 Ch 1

info: July 10. Khan demonstrates Morning Star's abilities to an assembly of delegates from nations in Southern Asia and the Middle East.
source: The Eugenics Wars: The Rise And Fall Of Khan Noonien Singh Vol 2 Ch 2

info: November 5. Seven and Lincoln are forced to destroy their base of operations in London during an attack by Khan's minions.
source: The Eugenics Wars: The Rise And Fall Of Khan Noonien Singh Vol 2 Ch 3-4

info: March 15. Walter Nichols joins Dr. Jeffrey Carlson, Shaun Christopher, Jackson Roykirk and Shannon O'Donnell at Area 51 to assist in the construction of the DY-100 sleeper ship.
source: The Eugenics Wars: The Rise And Fall Of Khan Noonien Singh Vol 2 Ch 5

info: June 14. Khan convenes a summit of the other world leaders conceived through the Chrysalis Project. When they refuse to follow his banner, Khan considers retaliating with Morning Star, but his advisor Ament convinces him to reconsider.
source: The Eugenics Wars: The Rise And Fall Of Khan Noonien Singh Vol 2 Ch 6, 8

info: September 10. Gary Seven relocates his headquarters to the Isle of Arran off the coast of Scotland.
source: The Eugenics Wars: The Rise And Fall Of Khan Noonien Singh Vol 2 Ch 9

info: September 30. Khan is lured to the Ajorra caves in central India by Vasily Hunyadi, a Balkan dictator and former Chrysalis child, who attempts to assassinate Khan by triggering an earthquake.
source: The Eugenics Wars: The Rise And Fall Of Khan Noonien Singh Vol 2 Ch 10

info: October 1. Roberta Lincoln continues her ongoing practice of feeding information on starship engineering to Shannon O'Donnell.
source: The Eugenics Wars: The Rise And Fall Of Khan Noonien Singh Vol 2 Ch 11

info: February 7. Khan's attempt to retaliate against Hunyadi is thwarted when the nuclear sub S.G.K. Kaur is struck by a mine.
source: The Eugenics Wars: The Rise And Fall Of Khan Noonien Singh Vol 2 Ch 12-13

info: April 21. Dr. Donald Williams of the Chrysalis Project offers to Khan the genetic sequence for a flesh-eating strain of strep-A developed by Sarina Kaur.
source: The Eugenics Wars: The Rise And Fall Of Khan Noonien Singh Vol 2 Ch 14

info: August 16. At Fort Cochise, Lincoln infiltrates the militia compound of Hawkeye Morrison, who has teamed up with Khan to eliminate both Hunyadi and Seven.
source: The Eugenics Wars: The Rise And Fall Of Khan Noonien Singh Vol 2 Ch 15-17

info: October 2. Khan begins human testing of his carnivorous bacteria.
source: The Eugenics Wars: The Rise And Fall Of Khan Noonien Singh Vol 2 Ch 18

info: November 14. Seven foils Morrison's attempt to release sarin gas in the Eurotunnel, then assists Lincoln in escaping from Morrison's bomb shelter.
source: The Eugenics Wars: The Rise And Fall Of Khan Noonien Singh Vol 2 Ch 19-20

info: March 17. Khan acquires over 200 bio-warheads from the former Soviet Union.
source: The Eugenics Wars: The Rise And Fall Of Khan Noonien Singh Vol 2 Ch 21

info: April 24. The crew of the Russian aircraft carrier Gorshkov is attacked by an alien entity.
September 5. A team of Amazon women storm Chrysalis Island and destroy Khan's arsenal of bio-weapons with a nuclear explosion.
source: The Eugenics Wars: The Rise And Fall Of Khan Noonien Singh Vol 2 Ch 22-23

info: January 5. Facing certain defeat at the hands of combined forces from multiple nations, Khan Noonien Singh accepts an offer from Gary Seven to leave the planet with 83 of his genetically engineered followers aboard the DY-100 sleeper ship, christened the S.S. Botany Bay.
source: The Eugenics Wars: The Rise And Fall Of Khan Noonien Singh Vol 2 Ch 24-27; Space Seed - Star Trek 2

info: January 5. In a battle with Captain Braxton of the 29th century, Voyager returns to Earth via a time rift. They are unknowingly assisted by Lucsly and Dulmer of the Department of Temporal Investigations.
J.R. Rasmussen resigns his/her job as a temporal researcher for the Deep Space Nine television series.
The deep space probe Nomad is launched.

June 21-22. Captain John Christopher, whose wife had left him following his abduction in 1969, struggles with conflicting memories while in a Massachusetts psychiatric ward, until this timeline is eliminated by the Temporal Integrity Commission.
The U.N.S.S. Icarus begins a sublight expedition to Alpha Centauri.

note: Federation gives the year as 2030, which contradicts the information given in Broken Bow and Metamorphosis.
info: Birth of Zefram Cochrane.
A Vulcan scout ship crash lands on Earth.

note: The Icarus was not a sleeper ship. The 30-year duration of its voyage is a predictable consequence of relativistic time distortion at very high sublight speeds.
info: The Icarus discovers sentient humanoid life in the Alpha Certauri system.
source: Strangers From The Sky - Author's Foreward

info: May 1. Colonel Green, founder of the Optimum movement, wages nuclear war upon the United States.
source: Star Trek 8: First Contact; Federation; The Savage Curtain - Star Trek 6

info: May 1. The residents of the Vanguard asteroid colony in orbit around Earth observe the nuclear detonations on the planet.
Zefram Cochrane discovers a 'breakthrough' in warp drive technology. Micah Brack begins funding his experiments.
source: Strangers From The Sky - Author's Foreward; Federation

info: August 9. During a warp field test by Cochrane's Project Phoenix, the Vanguard colony is accidentally transported about 200 light-years from Earth. Less than one month later, the colony is attacked by Naussicans, who kill nearly a third of the colonists.
Aboard the John Cabal, Zefram Cochrane demonstrates warp capability to Brack with a fluctuation superimpellor test sled.
April 6. Zephram Cochrane is visited by the crew of the Enterprise-D from 300 years in the future, who implore him to continue with his warp flight test despite a recent attack by the Borg.
April 6. Meanwhile, the Vanguard colony continues to practice radical genetic engineering so that their children mature faster and are better adapted to their environment.
April 7. Cochrane breaks the light barrier with the Phoenix. Vulcan makes first contact with Earth.
April 7. Dulmer and Lucsly of the Department of Temporal Investigations perform reconnaissance at Cochrane's Montana base to ensure that no corruption of the timeline has occurred.

note: The given year of 2061 is incorrect, as this would predate Cochrane's first manned test of warp drive.
info: March 19. Cochrane returns from his interstellar trip to Alpha Centauri on the Bonaventure, arriving at Christopher's Landing on Titan. The entire journey had taken 243 days. Shortly after his return, he departs again to flee Adrik Thorsen.

note: The text claims this to be the first encounter with Vulcans. Either the prior contact with Zefram Cochrane was kept secret, or else the author meant the first offworld contact initiated by an Earth vessel. This particular event appears to have paved the way toward diplomatic relations.
info: The U.N.S.S. Amity rescues a disabled Vulcan craft within the solar system.
source: Strangers From The Sky - Author's Foreward

info: The first diplomatic Vulcan delegation arrives on Earth.
source: Strangers From The Sky - Author's Foreward

info: Backstory
The planet Trill is attacked by the L'Dira for refusing an offer of trade. Lela Dax, having communicated with the L'Dira prior to the attack, is tried for treason. T'Pau of Vulcan pays her a visit.
source: First Steps - The Lives Of Dax

note: Encounter At Farpoint speaks of the 'post-atomic horror' in 2079. Therefore, it seems that Col. Thorsen brought about a revival of the Optimum movement and a second nuclear war in the 2070s.
info: June. Cochrane flees the aftermath of World War 3 and takes up permanent residence on the Alpha Centauri colony.

note: This timeline will be eliminated when Captain Spock and Ensign Kirk from Second History travel back in time to foil the assassination.
info: Romulan androids from the future assassinate Dr. Palmer, thus weakening support for space exploration and ultimately preventing the formation of the U.F.P. The Earth will eventually join the Interstellar Alliance of Planets, founded by Vulcan. The Romulans refer to this timeline as Second History.
Zefram Cochrane speaks at the groundbreaking ceremony for the Warp 5 Complex.

note: The text gives the year as 2117, which would be before Cochrane speaks at the Warp 5 Complex.
info: April. At age 87, Cochrane leaves his home on Alpha Centauri and disappears into space.
11 year-old Jonathan Archer visits the Sol Museum of Aeronautical Science, and spends time with T'Rama, eventual mother to Sarek.
source: A Girl For Every Star - SNW 5

info: Jonathan Archer builds a model spaceship with his father, Henry.
The meeting of the First Federation Congress. Presumably, early drafts of the Articles of Federation would have begun at this time.
At the Roykirk Summer School on Earth, fifteen year-old Charles Tucker develops a proposal for a phase conduit cooling system.
October 5. Backstory
April 9. Time travel.

April 16. The Earth Starfleet vessel Enterprise NX-01 is launched with Captain Jonathan Archer in command. Sub-commander T'Pol is the Vulcan liason and science officer. Commander Charles Tucker is Chief Engineer. Lt. Malcolm Reed is at Tactical, Ensign Hoshi Sato at Communications, Ensign Travis Mayweather at Helm, and Dr. Phlox is a Denobulan member of the Vulcan Interspecies Medical Exchange.
April 16. Hoshi becomes ill from nurturing an unhatched Vulcan firebird.
April 16. Book.
April 16. On Beta Aurigae 7, a landing party led by T'Pol discovers archaeological evidence of the Zalkat Union, including documentation of the four deadly artifacts of Malkus the Mighty.
source: The Brave And The Bold Book 1: Discovery

info: September 10. Aboard the Enterprise, crewman Daniels reveals himself to be an agent fighting a temporal cold war against the Suliban.

note: The chronological references in this story are wildly contradictory and have been mostly ignored.
info: Book
Archer and Mayweather are held captive at the Tandaran detention complex along with Suliban prisoners.
Dr. Phlox, assigned to decontaminate crewman Daniels's quarters, attempts time travel to save Xesophia, who drowned on Denobula twenty-eight years earlier.
Book
The Enterprise rescues the crew of the Lost Moon, an Earth colony ship.
Two crewmen from the Enterprise are murdered by the Kolyati.
source: The Shoulders Of Giants: Prologue - SNW 5

info: Book
On the planet Druzilum, Archer acts to preserve the martyrdom of a man destined to become a religious icon.
Book
Book
Book
The crew of Enterprise begins to suffer inexplicable fits of narcolepsy.

note: This is ninety years prior to the events of The Final Reflection Part 3. This is described as the 'incorporation' of the U.F.P., a term also used in Federation to describe the events of 2161. However, it is well established that a Federation existed in some form during the First Romulan War. In Strangers From The Sky, the date is given as 2087, which contradicts Metamorphosis and Broken Bow.
info: The Articles of Federation are signed at Babel. Participants include Earth, Andor and Rigel, but not Vulcan. Initially, this is merely an alliance, with planetary governments still retaining all of their sovereignty.
source: The Final Reflection - TOS 16 Part 3; The Abode Of Life - TOS 6; The Romulan Way - TOS 35 Ch 12

info: August 9. The Vanguard colony, whose residents have now evolved into a quadruped race known as the Neyel, falls into an interspatial rift and emerges 210,000 light-years away, in the center of the Small Magellanic Cloud.
The first major war with the Romulan Empire begins with the destruction of the USS Balboa. The initial conflict will last four years.
source: Rihannsu 2: The Romulan Way - TOS 35 Ch 12; My Brother's Keeper: Republic - TOS 85; Federation

info: Romulans capture the Heisenberg in an attempt to obtain Terran warp technology. Tobin Dax and Skon of Vulcan reclaim the ship with the aid of a transporter prototype.
source: Dead Man's Hand - The Lives Of Dax

info: The First Romulan War ends with the Treaty of Algernon. Vulcan pledges to join a new, amalgamated Federation.
In the aftermath of the Romulan conflict, the U.F.P. Constitution is signed and Starfleet is commissioned as the armed services via the Paris Charter.

note: The descendants of the Verdun claim knowledge of the Enterprise, which obviously must refer to the NX-01, though Riker mistakenly calls it Constitution-class.
info: Captain Lucien Murat and the crew of the USS Verdun are stranded on Torgu-Va during a war with the Tarn. They and their descendants will remain stranded for 204 years.

note: In the novel Sarek, his father is said to be Solkar. Most other sources agree that Solkar is in fact his grandfather.
info: Birth of Sarek, son of Skon.
In the Small Magellanic Cloud, the People of Neyel succeed in capturing a warp-capable vessel.
The policy of cultural non-interference is established as Starfleet's Prime Directive.
source: Double Helix 5: Double Or Nothing - TNG 55

note: Though this occurs in the interim after the Romulan War, the text indicates that the Romulans view the war as ongoing. This is not surprising, given that the Romulans continued to build and mobilize their forces during peacetime.
info: The Romulan cruiser Scorah abducts a Reyan exploratory vessel and kills everyone aboard.
The People of Neyel land their vessel on the world of Oghen, offering to share technology with the inhabitants in return for the use of the planet's resources.

note: Blish's novelization of Balance Of Terror contradicts the teleplay, which states that over a century had passed since the war. Duane's novel follows Blish's record of events, including the assertion that the conflict lasted 25 years. Therefore, we must assume that a protracted conflict resumed following the major war and was not conclusively resolved until this time. Negotiation of the treaty was urged by 'Ambassador' Sarek. Though not yet Ambassador Plenipotentiary, according to Spock's World he was likely posted to the Vulcan Embassy at this time.
info: Following twenty-five years of continuing hostility, the Romulan Neutral Zone is established by the Treaty of Trianguli, negotiated via subspace without any representatives ever meeting face-to-face. No contact will occur between the races for the next fifty years.
source: Rihannsu 2: The Romulan Way - TOS 35 Ch 12; Balance Of Terror - Star Trek 1

note: Described as first contact between the U.F.P. and the Klingon empire. This may be the first formal contact with the Federation, although Broken Bow establishes that Klingons had contact with Terrans prior to the founding of the U.F.P. One may assume that this is the incident that touched off fifty years of hostilities according to Day Of The Dove.
info: The USS Sentry meets with the Klingon vessel IKV Devisor.
Following the death of Drech'tor Hanif Wafiyy, the new leadership of the Neyel declare themselves absolute rulers over the planet Oghen.
Sarek marries T'Rea and conceives his first son, Sybok. The marriage is anulled when T'Rea decides to pursue the priesthood.
Birth of Leonard H. E. McCoy.

note: The year is given as 2212, and the length of Sarek's stay on Earth is said to have been 50 years. Both are problematic.
info: Sarek returns to Vulcan following an extended internship as a cultural attache on Earth and is appointed Ambassador Plenipotentiary to the U.F.P. Shortly thereafter, he meets Amanda Greyson.
Five year-old Sybok's mother T'Rea is condemned for teaching about Sha Ka Ree.
source: Star Trek 5: The Final Frontier - Prologue

info: June. Courtship of Sarek and Amanda.
September 16. Marriage of Sarek and Amanda.
source: Sarek Ch 5; Spock's World - Vulcan Seven

info: November 12. Birth of Spock, son of Sarek.
source: Sarek Ch 5; Spock's World - Vulcan Seven

info: December. Nine year-old Montgomery Scott becomes ill after eating a Danish lobster salad with radishes.
source: Bum Radish: Five Spins On A Turquoise Reindeer - SNW 6

note: This takes place six years prior to Part 2. Considering that these events are all framed within a novel read by Kirk, they may be apocryphal.
info: A secret faction within the Klingon Empire attempts to forge a treaty with the Romulans. Once discovered, Vrenn Khemara assumes a new identity (Krenn) to avoid assassination.
Birth of James Tiberius Kirk.
McCoy is nine years old.

note: The story is internally inconsistent, giving Spock's age here as seven (Vulcan years?).
info: December 7. Young Spock runs away from home.
An adult Spock arrives from the future to prevent his own death.

Upon developing dilithium-focused warp drive, Captain Krenn sutai-Rustazh serves as the first Klingon ambassador to the U.F.P. in the 22 years since first contact. While on Earth, he plays a game of chess with young Spock, age eight.

note: A letter from George Sr. to his children is dated May 10, 2183, obviously a little off the mark.
info: The Federation's first starship, the USS Enterprise, is secretly commissioned early to rescue colonists stranded aboard the Rosenberg. Captain Robert April commands the mission, accompanied by George S. Kirk, Security Chief of Starbase Two and father of George Jr. and James (age ten). Wishing to avoid yet another major war, Field Primus t'Cael Zaniidor Kilyle helps April to escape from Romulan space.
Four years after formalizing diplomatic relations, the Klingons attempt to influence member worlds of the U.F.P. to vote for dissolution of the Federation.
McCoy is seventeen years old.
Montgomery Scott formulates the Aberdeen Solution, which disproves the Perera Theory of photon torpedo explosions.
McCoy meets Emony Dax during a gymnastics competition at Ole Miss.
source: Old Souls - The Lives Of Dax

info: October 10. Slightly over a year after beginning its 'official' maiden voyage, the Enterprise is attacked by Klingon Commander Kor while attempting to deliver supplies to Tarsus 4.
source: Though Hell Should Bar The Way - Enterprise Logs

note: Some sources give Kirk's age here as 14. We assume the figure is rounded up.
info: October 10. Young James Kirk witnesses the massacre of four thousand colonists on Tarsus 4 by Kodos the Executioner. Kirk is rescued by Sarek, but his memory of the ambassador is suppressed.
source: A Flag Full Of Stars - TOS 54; Avenger Ch 1; The Conscience Of The King - Star Trek 1

info: Spock, along with a group of Vulcan and human students, is taken hostage by Sered, a Romulan sympathizer. Spock escapes with David Rabin, who will later convince Spock to join Starfleet.

George Kirk and his family are forced to flee the Federation Embassy on Grex when racial violence erupts in the streets. Due to interference from the Janus Gate on Tlaoli 4, 14 year-old James Kirk disappears and is replaced by his adult self from 2265.
source: The Janus Gate Book 3: Past Prologue - TOS

info: At age sixteen, Spock chooses to enter Starfleet Academy against the wishes of his father, causing a rift that will last eighteen years.
source: Sarek Ch 12; Vulcan's Glory - TOS 44; Journey To Babel - Star Trek 4

note: This is 43 years before the framing story, whereas the text claims 45 years.
info: George Kirk Sr. allows young James, age sixteen, to accompany him on an expedition to the planet Faramond. They depart from the shuttle bay of the Enterprise, where Jim Kirk meets Captain April and sets foot on the bridge. Later, they are attacked by Roy Moss and the pirate ship Shark, and are rescued by April.

Kirk enters Starfleet Academy. While on a training mission aboard the USS Republic, Kirk records a mistake made by Benjamin Finney in the duty log. Finney will come to believe that this report has slowed his advancement in Starfleet.
source: My Brother's Keeper: Republic - TOS 85; Court Martial - Star Trek 2

info: Kirk is awarded the Palm Leaf of Axanar for his achievement on a peace mission following Captain Garth of Izar's victory over the Klingons.
source: Court Martial - Star Trek 2; Whom Gods Destroy - Star Trek 5

info: Ensign Spock graduates from the Academy and serves as Assistant Science Officer on a space cutter ship.

note: According to Where No Man Has Gone Before, Kirk was a lieutenant when Mitchell joined the Academy. Friedman's story tries to reconcile this by suggesting Kirk achieved the rank in his second year as a student. A more reasonable solution would be to place Mitchell's academy years a bit later.
info: Cadets James Kirk and Gary Mitchell receive a commendation from Captain Bannock for their actions during a patrol of the Klingon Neutral Zone.
After nine years, April announces Christopher Richard Pike as his successor to the captaincy of the Enterprise.
McCoy, age 26, is assigned as Junior Medical Officer aboard the USS Republic under Captain Hillios and CMO Vincent Bando. On the planet Ssan, he saves the life of a ruthless assassin.
source: Shadows On The Sun - Book 2; The Better Man - TOS 72

info: Spock is promoted to Lieutenant Junior Grade and serves as Science Officer on the USS Artemis.
Prior to his graduation from the Academy, Kirk serves as a midshipman aboard the USS Farragut.
McCoy assigned Chief Medical Officer aboard the USS Richard Feynman. After seven months, he transfers to the USS Koop as a Junior M.O.
Kirk modifies the Kobayashi Maru simulation, enabling him to rescue the ship.
source: The Kobayashi Maru - TOS 47; Star Trek 2: The Wrath Of Khan; A Test Of Character - SNW 7

info: Ensign James T. Kirk, age 22, receives a Decoration Of Valor for his injuries sustained while battling the pirates of Epsilon Canaris 3 aboard the USS Farragut. McCoy oversees Kirk's rehabilitation on Starbase 7, and later Kirk visits his home on Centaurus (aka Alpha Centauri 4). McCoy's daughter Joanna is nine years old.
Spock is promoted to full Lieutenant and assigned Second Officer aboard the USS Enterprise under Captain Pike. Lt. Montgomery Scott is assigned to Engineering.

note: The Enterprise is said to be only nine years old.
info: Yeoman Colt signs aboard the Enterprise. The Federation negotiates a dilithium mining agreement with the Eremoids.

note: According to the details given in the televised version of The Menagerie, the Talosian incident would be in 2253, while Spock's assignment to the Enterprise would be in 2252. However, these dates are incompatible with Spock's service record in Vulcan's Glory.
info: Captain Pike is captured by the Talosians, who have incredible power to create illusion.
Pike's Enterprise makes first contact with the Calligar after passing through a temporal rift that opens every 33 years.
Pike backstory.
The USS Hood makes first contact with the Rey.
Lieutenant Kirk survives the attack of the vampire cloud creature upon the Farragut, which kills half the crew, including Captain Garrovick.
source: My Brother's Keeper: Constitution - TOS 86; Obsession - Star Trek 9; The Ashes Of Eden

info: Serving aboard the USS Constitution with Gary Mitchell, Second Officer Kirk is forced to take command when Captain Augenthaler and First Officer Hirota are incapacitated on Sordinia 4.
McCoy signs aboard the Constitution to work under CMO Christina Velasquez.
Pike saves the lives of his senior staff while surveying Corinthia 4.
Pike's Enterprise responds to a distress call from the freighter Lisander, which is under attack from a Merkaan named Hamesaad Dreen.
Prior to his next promotion, Kirk serves under Captain Wilhelm Schang aboard the Tresher.
Lieutenant Commander James T. Kirk spends a year on the planet Shad.
source: The Covenant Of The Crown - TOS 4 p 23-29

info: Kirk serves as Second Officer aboard the Aeolus, and has a relationship with Cecilia Simons.
Death of Hikaru Sulu's grandfather, Tetsuo Inomata. Sulu survives the Kobayashi Maru scenario by refusing to aid the distressed ship.
Kirk serves as First Officer aboard the USS Bonhomme Richard.

info: While serving together aboard the Lydia Sutherland, Kirk and Mitchell are both seriously injured in an incident at Ghioghe.
Chekov completes the Aslan training scenario, surviving for three days in the midst of an 'assassin'.

note: McIntyre's novel stretches the limits of credibility, forcing the reader to assume that the entire bridge crew (except Spock) transferred elsewhere prior to Where No Man Has Gone Before, only to return to their previous posts immediately thereafter. For those who would eliminate certain novels to preserve continuity, the storyline in Friedman's Brother's Keeper omnibus is probably preferred.
info: March. Pike is promoted to Commodore. Just prior to his 30th birthday, James T. Kirk is commissioned as captain of the USS Enterprise. Commander Spock is chosen by Starfleet to serve as First Officer over Kirk's objections. Kirk selects McCoy to be Chief Medical Officer. Montgomery Scott is Chief Engineer, Nyota Uhura is Communications Officer, Hikaru Sulu is Helmsman, Janice Rand is Yeoman with bridge duty. Ensign Chekov has low watch on the bridge. Navigator Gary Mitchell is still recovering from his injuries at Ghioghe. Kirk's relationship with Carol Marcus ends.
March. Sulu transfers to Astrophysics, replaced at the helm by Lee Kelso.
March. McCoy requests leave on Starbase 6 (perhaps to attend to his ill father). Dr. Mark Piper, David Bailey and Dr. Elizabeth Dehner sign aboard.

March. While investigating the planet Kapeshet, the landing party is transported back in time to witness a secret first contact with Vulcans on Earth. The party's memories of the event are suppressed.

March. Five months into the mission, the Enterprise discovers a vessel in the Mandylion Rift which had fled from the Totality in the Greater Magellanic Cloud. Lt. Hounslaw Tanaka, in a competition to win the vessel, becomes the first fatality under Kirk's command.

note: Said to occur immediately after the Dimorus mission, when Gary Mitchell is hit with a poisoned dart. However, Captain's Peril establishes that Mitchell left the ship for over three months to recuperate. Must occur after Captain's Peril given the deaths of two crewmen.
info: While on a secret mission along the Klingon Neutral Zone, the Enterprise is commandeered by renegade Klingons led by Commander Kang.
Following the death of his father, McCoy goes on a medical relief mission to Capella 4.
source: My Brother's Keeper: Constitution - TOS 86; Friday's Child - Star Trek 3

info: The Enterprise attempts to cross the Energy Barrier at the outer edge of the galaxy, where the disoriented and incorporeal being Q is trapped.
Gary Mitchell, Elizabeth Dehner and Lee Kelso are killed on Delta Vega following the encounter with the Galactic Barrier.
source: Where No Man Has Gone Before - Star Trek 8; My Brother's Keeper: Republic - TOS 85

note: Kirk is surprised to hear Piper's request for a discharge. However, earlier in Strangers From The Sky, Piper's retirement date had already been set.
info: Services for Lee Kelso are held aboard the Enterprise. Lt. Daniel Alden, Yeoman Barbara Smith and Dr. Mark Piper transfer off the ship. Lt. Hikaru Sulu is (re)assigned as helmsman.

note: It is inferred that Uhura, Bailey and Rand are coming aboard the Enterprise for the first time. Also, McCoy claims to have served with Kirk previously aboard the Constitution, but not the Enterprise.
info: Uhura, Bailey and Rand are reassigned to the bridge crew. McCoy returns as Chief Medical Officer. Kirk delivers the eulogy at Mitchell's funeral.
Audrid Dax participates in a classified mission with Fleet Captain Pike.
source: Sins Of The Mother - The Lives Of Dax

info: Having completely plundered the planet of Oghen, the Neyel Hegemony sends forth a fleet of ships to conquer and colonize additional worlds.
Following a minor refit of the Enterprise and changes in uniform design, the famed 'five-year mission' begins.
The Enterprise investigates a self-imposed quarantine of the planet Timshel, and discovers the citizens are enslaved to a computer that produces an artificial euphoria.
The Enterprise rescues member of the Anjiri and Nykuss, but does not log the incident to protect the location of their homeworld.

note: The text states that this is near the end of the five-year mission, which is inconsistent with all other references to Joanna's age.
info: McCoy's daughter Joanna turns eighteen.
Diplomatic relations established with the alien Balok of the First Federation.
The Enterprise responds to a distress call issued by career criminal Harry Mudd.
A transporter accident splits Kirk into two entities.
On planet M-113, a creature capable of psychic disguise makes its way onto the Enterprise and attacks the crew for their body salts.
A virus contracted on Psi 2000 spreads throughout the crew, causing wildly erratic behavior. A cold start of the warp engines throws the ship back in time three days.

The Enterprise crew travels to Tlaoli 4 to retrieve a survey team, and discovers an ancient time portal. Kirk is inadvertently exchanged with his own self from the past, while Sulu is swapped with his future self.

source: The Conscience Of The King - Star Trek 1

Framing story, shortly before Pike's accident.

Fleet Captain Pike saves the lives of seven cadets aboard a training vessel, but is exposed to massive amounts of radiation. He soon loses all motor control and is confined to a mobile life-support carriage on Starbase 11.
Commanded by Spock, the Galileo 7 shuttlecraft is stranded on Taurus 2.

Kirk is forced to jetisson an observation pod occupied by Benjamin Finney. The investigation reveals negligence by Kirk, but he is absolved of wrongdoing when it is revealed that Finney is alive and has doctored the record tapes.
The Enterprise unwittingly spreads a computer virus to five planetary systems. A 'virtual' alien civilization is discovered in orbit around Tyrtaeus. Rand is still aboard.

Kirk investigates the murder of a Draqqi diplomat.

note: According to Spock in the television episode The Menagerie Part 1, this is thirteen years after the incident on Talos 4. In Journey To Babel, it has been eighteen years since Spock left home for Starfleet. Subtract the one year between the episodes, and we have only four years for young Spock to have received all his academy training, promotion to full lieutenant, and assignment as Second Officer aboard the Enterprise. This is incredible, even for a Vulcan; plus, it contradicts Spock's service record given in Dorothy Fontana's Vulcan's Glory. Fortunately, since the 'thirteen years' figure never appears anywhere in print, we can ignore it in good conscience.
info: Spock is promoted to full commander. Pike is kidnapped by Spock, who diverts the Enterprise to Talos 4 without authorization. Spock's court martial is dismissed when Pike chooses to remain with the Talosians, who provide him the illusion of good health.

info: War breaks out between the Federation and Klingons, and the Enterprise attempts to contact Organia via long-range transport by using tachyon particles. The signal is reflected back, causing duplicate Spocks.

note: The events of Spock Must Die! include a massive six-month war with the Klingon Empire, as well as a judgement handed down by the Organians depriving the Klingons of spaceflight for a thousand years. Obviously, it is quite impossible to reconcile this with the rest of the Trek chronology. However, at the end of Mudd's Angels, the Enterprise is flung backward in time at least six months. Therefore, one must assume that the events of Spock Must Die! occur within that period, thus becoming a divergent timeline. Spock, Messiah! refers to events in Spock Must Die!, and therefore must also belong to the alternate timeline. To appease those who worship at the shrine of the Okudachron, you may even assume that all of the Bantam novels, as well as the Animated Series, are a part of this divergent reality as well; Also Prime Directive, which could never fit into established Trek history.

info: Book

note: The Malurian system was wiped out in The Changeling, but they feature prominently in this story, suggesting placement prior to that episode. However, the presence of Dr. M'Benga disallows it. Granted, the star system in The Changeling was Omega Ceti, whereas Friedman gives Alpha Maluria, so it is possible that the race had colonized many different systems. More troubling is that David Marcus is ten years old. David is twenty during The Wrath Of Khan, which is consistent with the idea that Kirk and Carol broke off their relationship just prior to his captaincy. If the story occurs 'halfway though the five-year mission' (per the historian's note), David would still be a toddler. Even according to Okuda, he would only be about six.
info: Klingons capture a terraforming colony on Beta Canzandia 3. Commander Kruge is promoted to Captain. Kirk meets his son, David Marcus.

Primary hull is jettisoned after explosion. Enterprise is refit at Starbase 12. Chekov is promoted to Lieutenant. Gray uniforms introduced. More refitting occurs after sustaining damage from Tomarii and Romulan warships.

Five-year mission ends, and the Enterprise returns to spacedock. Kirk is promoted to Admiral. Uhura is promoted to Lt. Commander. Scott is promoted to Commander. McCoy and Spock request to be discharged. Spock returns to Vulcan to undergo Kolinahr.
While vacationing with Chekov on the planet Demora, Sulu meets Ling 'Susan' Sui, and unknowingly fathers a child.
source: The Captain's Daughter Part 2: First Date - TOS 76

note: Sadly, this story represents the second time Chekov has been promoted to Lieutenant. Perhaps the earlier change was only a field promotion. The year has been adjusted from the given date of 2269.
info: December. Chekov is accused of killing Dr. Mark Piper with a Klingon disruptor, while Sulu is arrested for theft of information on the Romulan cloaking device. A conspiracy is discovered to incite a war between the Klingons and Romulans.

note: The year has been adjusted from the given date of 2270.
info: Kirk and McCoy visit the Cochrane monument on Titan.
Nine year-old Tuvok's sehlat, Wari, is euthanized following a severe injury.

note: The story occurs during the Apollo Tricentennial, presumably commemorating the end of the entire Apollo space program in 1972.
info: July. Eighteen months following the end of the mission. G'Dath, a Klingon instructor working on Earth, is kidnapped by Klingons following his discovery of a new propulsion system.
source: A Flag Full Of Stars - TOS 54

info: July. Book
July. Captain William Decker discovers two Romulan operatives among the crew completing the Enterprise refit.

July. An immense spacecraft indentifying itself as V'ger threatens to destroy the Earth. Joined by the rest of the crew from the first five-year mission, Kirk takes command of the Enterprise from Captain Decker, who is lost during the encounter. Chekov is Chief of Security.
source: Star Trek 1: The Motion Picture - TOS 1

info: July. Book.
July. Book.
July. Book.
Kirk, Scott, Sulu and Chekov are stranded in the Hohweyn system aboard the shuttlecraft Halley.
The Enterprise encounters the alien Weyland during a conflict with the Klingons.
Commander Spock takes a two-week leave on Vulcan while the Enterprise transports a diplomatic party of Kaldorni.
Spock rescues Saavik from Hellguard, and extends his leave to a full year to help assimilate Saavik into Vulcan culture, eventually preparing her for training at the Academy.
Spock utilizes a mind meld to help bring his cousin Elizabeth Fitzhugh out of a comatose state.
Seven years after 'Amok Time'.

note: Internal references would place the story in 2272, which contradicts the Historian's Note and Chekov's rank.
info: The Empyreans renew their treaty with the Federation. McCoy meets his second daughter, Anna.
Planetwide mental illness strikes the planet Nordstral due to an over-harvesting of magnetic plankton.
The Romulan space station Reltah drifts into Federation space, disabled by an energy-consuming parasite.
The Enterprise battles two Orion destroyers and a saboteur in the sector between Orion and Andor.

note: There is no easy way to reconcile the various Mudd stories, all of which claim to be his first meeting with Kirk's crew since 'I, Mudd.' Crew rank implies that this story is during the original five-year mission; but given the established timeframes of Mudd In Your Eye and Mudd's Passion, plus a gap of several years before this story, a post-TMP placement is necessary.
info: Harry Mudd agrees to stop altering the habitat of the Saganicus gas-giant floaters in return for Spock and Uhura's assistance in creating an Enterprise simulator.
Kirk finds himself aboard a Klingon vessel and is told that he has travelled into the future.

note: Despite McCoy's comment in TMP that Chapel is an M.D., we must assume that she had not yet completed her practicals and thesis.
info: The Enterprise is selected to test the new inversion drive propulsion system. Lia Burke is trained in sickbay as Chapel begins work on her doctoral thesis. Colin Matlock serves as Security Chief while Chekov returns to Navigation.

note: Minor inconsistencies in crew rank. Chekov and Sulu are both lieutenants.
info: The Enterprise rescues Vulcan prisoners from a Romulan research lab with the assistance of Ael t'Rllaillieu, a Romulan defector.
source: Rihannsu 1: My Enemy, My Ally - TOS 18

info: McCoy's fiftieth birthday. Eighteen years after Kirk's extended mission on Shad.
source: The Covenant Of The Crown - TOS 4

info: Christine Chapel leaves to complete her doctorate. Lia Burke replaces her as head nurse. Ingrit Tomson returns as head of Security. Kirk has recently celebrated a birthday.

After two years in the field (presumably since the return of Spock in 2274), the Enterprise returns to Earth for a month-long retrofit. A proposal among Vulcans to secede from the Federation is narrowly defeated. Kirk meets K's't'lk for the first time. Death of T'Pau.
McCoy, age 50, is abducted from the USS Vega by Romulans. One 'standard' year after My Enemy, My Ally, and eight years after The Enterprise Incident.
November. Book.

note: The Rihannsu novels 2-4 clearly follow Spock's World, especially given the appearance of K's't'lk in Swordhunt; however, most of the crew ranks are incorrect for this period.
info: November. Onset of the Second Romulan War.

note: Saavik is still attending the academy six years later in The Wrath Of Khan; this is consistent with the fact that she achieves the rank of Lieutenant while still a student. The story contains an inference that T'Pau is still alive... and in fact, a Vulcan matriarch with the same name is very much alive decades later in Vulcan's Heart.
info: Saavik enters Starfleet Academy. A Romulan warbird is discovered adrift in Federation space.

note: Many of the novels in this period feature the red 'tunic-style' uniforms and Chekov as a Lieutenant Commander. Unfortunately, the New Earth series chronicles not only the introduction of the new uniforms but also Chekov's promotion and transfer to the Reliant. Therefore, uniform style and Chekov's rank must be ignored during this period.
info: The renegade Klingon Captain Kasak sutai-Khomezh attempts to trigger a war with the Federation. Admiral Randolph Morrow has become Starfleet Chief of Operations.

After crash-landing a shuttle on Mars resulting in the death of Lt. Mears, McCoy meets Irum, who sends McCoy back in time to avoid the crash. His action spawns a genetic mutation called Irumodic Syndrome that will eventually affect Jean-Luc Picard.
source: The Name Of The Cat - SNW 4

note: For whatever reason, Chekov's new assignment is substantially delayed until the Belle Terre expedition.
info: The Akkalla-Chorym Alliance is formed. Chekov is offered assignment as First Officer of the USS Reliant. Kirk decides to become an instructor at the Academy. The Enterprise is recommissioned as a training vessel under command of Spock (soon to be promoted to Captain).
Sulu meets his daughter Demora following Ling Sui's death. He refuses assignment as First Officer of the Bozeman, and instead becomes an instructor at the Academy.

Launch of the USS Bozeman under Captain Bateson. Kirk temporarily takes the Enterprise out of the Academy training program to investigate a Klingon incursion into Federation space. The Bozeman disappears into a temporal distortion.

note: Year is given as 2279, which is eight years prior to ST:TFF per the Okuda timeline.
info: The USS Gagarin is attacked by Klingons near the neutral zone, and self-destructs in an attempt to avoid capture. Nonetheless, many crew members including Cmdr. Stephen Garrovick are taken prisoner.
source: In The Name Of Honor - TOS 97 Ch 1-2

info: Book
Kirk receives a communique from Bela Oxmyx, now President of the Iotian Union.
source: A Piece Of The Pie - SNW 6

info: Captain Spock commands the Enterprise on a two-month training cruise. Cadet Saavik is aboard.
source: Just Another Little Training Cruise - Enterprise Logs

info: Audrid Dax writes a letter to her daughter Neema, explaining the events surrounding her father's death fifteen years earlier.
source: Sins Of The Mother - The Lives Of Dax

info: Kirk receives a second message from Bela Oxmyx, who had successfully followed Kirk's advice in choosing a successor to his Presidency.
source: A Piece Of The Pie - SNW 6

info: Kirk accepts an offer to return to the Enterprise and lead the 72 vessels of the Belle Terre colonial expedition on a nine-month journey to Occult 4. Captain Spock and the rest of the Enterprise crew agree to join the mission.
source: Wagon Train To The Stars - TOS 89

note: The text gives the year as 2272, and the cover blurbs support this date by placing the New Earth series shortly after the V'ger incident. However, the details of the story clearly support a much later date: Spock is a captain, Kirk is an instructor, the Enterprise is a training vessel, Chekov is about to be transferred, etc. Furthermore, the uniform alterations would not occur so soon after the change in ST:TMP. Nonetheless, we must contend with several problems, including the whereabouts of Sulu's daughter and the fact that Chekov hasn't yet received the promotion to First Officer of the Reliant as mentioned in Deep Domain.
info: October 31. New red Starfleet uniforms are introduced.
source: Wagon Train To The Stars - TOS 89

info: The Belle Terre expedition is attacked by an alliance of two local racesthe Kauld and the Bloodalong with Orion pirates under direction of a renegade colonist named Billy Maidenshore.
source: Wagon Train To The Stars - TOS 89

info: Following the colonization of Occult 4, nearly half of the planet is obliterated by a release of pressurized quasar olivium within one of its moons.
A conspiracy to flood the Belle Terre colony with olivium is discovered by Sulu and Uhura.
Chekov transfers to the USS Reliant as First Officer. The Kauld attack Belle Terre with an olivium-powered laser constructed on a comet.
A plague of nanoprobes infect the Belle Terre colonists with a deadly siliconic gel.

The cruiser Peleliu arrives at Belle Terre to relieve the Enterprise but is destroyed by Kauld warships. The colonists construct a new ship, the Challenger, using components from other colonial vessels. Following the surrender of the Kauld and the apprehending of Maidenshore, the Enterprise returns to U.F.P. space.
McCoy learns from his grandson Conner, age two, that his ex-wife Jocelyn had remarried and joined the diplomatic corps.

note: The story mentions that Spock has resigned from Starfleet and intends to return to Vulcan, suggesting placement just after The Lost Years. However, the story also states that Spock is a 'former captain' and implies that Admiral Kirk reports to Admiral Morrow; therefore, we must assume that Spock made this decision in the post-TMP timeframe only to reconsider soon after.
info: A representative from Sigma Iotia visits Kirk at his home to pay him his 'piece of the action'.
Book
Book
source: Exodus - Gateways: What Lay Beyond - Challenger

info: The Enterprise is (again/still) under Kirk's temporary command, conducting routine missions and training cruises. Lt. Saavik is aboard under Spock's tutelage.
Demora Sulu visits Starfleet academy, where Hikaru is teaching a course in astronavigation, and briefly meets Saavik, Boothby and Admiral Kirk.
At age 20, Tuvok is accepted to Starfleet Academy.

note: Several problems here. The story takes place two days before the scheduled launch of the Excelsior, which is during the events of The Search For Spock when Saavik would be investigating the Genesis planet. We must assume that this is an earlier launch date which was postponed following the accident. Also, Saavik is consistently addressed as 'cadet' though she must hold a commissioned rank by this time. Finally, several references in the television series indicate that Torias would not have been joined until sometime between 2286-88.
info: Saavik works with Torias Dax on the Transwarp development project. Torias is killed when the shuttle Infinity attempts the first test flight.
Main story, one month before The Wrath Of Khan, 14.5 years after Yesterday's Son.
Main story.

March. Kirk's 51st birthday. His son, David Marcus, is twenty. Khan Noonian Singh captures the USS Reliant and attacks a research station in an attempt to locate the Genesis device. The Enterprise investigates and is attacked. After the battle, Captain Spock dies from radiation burns suffered while saving the ship from the detonation of the device. Prior to his death, he transfers his katra to McCoy.
source: Star Trek 2: The Wrath Of Khan

info: March. David Marcus struggles to accept the knowledge that James Kirk is his father.

note: March. The text gives the date of March 14, 2285. The Genesis Wave dates Spock's death on March 26, 2285.
info: Sarek and Amanda learn of Spock's death.

March. Kirk and crew steal the Enterprise from spacedock and travel to the Genesis planet, where Spock's regenerated body is discovered. Kirk's son David is killed by Klingons under command of Captain Kruge. The Enterprise is destroyed when Kirk orders a self-destruct. The crew capture Kruge's warbird and go into exile on Vulcan, where Spock's katra is reunited with his body.
source: Star Trek 3: The Search For Spock

info: March. Prior to its destruction, the Enterprise computer ponders its own sentience.
March. Joran Dax is found to be a serial murderer and is killed by one of his potential victims. The Trill Symbiosis Commission covers up all evidence that Joran Belar was ever joined.
source: Allegro Ouroboros In D Minor - The Lives Of Dax

info: March. In an alternate future, the Federation has been at war with the Gorn Hegemony for seventeen years. Via the Janus Gate, a young Sulu arrives from 2265 and assists Chekov in an attack upon the Tesseract Fortress on the planet Basaraba.
source: The Janus Gate Book 2: Future Imperfect - TOS

info: Demora Sulu stays with Janice Rand during her father's exile on Vulcan. Rand transfers to Starfleet Command.

A probe from deep space arrives at Earth and broadcasts a message toward the oceans, threatening to destroy the planet when there is no response. Kirk and crew time travel to twentieth century Earth in the warbird to retrieve humpback whales capable of communicating with the probe. Kirk is reduced in rank and commissioned as Captain of the Enterprise-A.
Story.
Book
source: To Reign In Hell: The Exile Of Khan Noonien Singh

info: Scotty assists Dr. Gillian Taylor in attempting to determine why the whales George and Gracie have fallen ill.
While investigating an uprising on Nimbus 3, Spock's half-brother Sybok incites a mutiny among the Enterprise crew, and takes the ship beyond the Great Barrier at the galactic center.
Book

note: Year is given as 2287, per the Okuda timeline.
info: With the assistance of Koloth, Kirk and Sulu rescue the remaining survivors of the Gagarin from a Klingon prison camp. Gorkon becomes Chancellor of the Klingon High Council.
source: In The Name Of Honor - TOS 97

note: Dillard's novelization places this event seven years prior to Generations. Note that the screenplay gives nine years, which would be prior to TWOK on the Okuda timeline.
info: Kirk buys a log cabin on Earth with his girlfriend, Antonia, whom he had met two years earlier. After considering retirement, he decides instead to return to Starfleet.

Tuvok graduates from the Academy and breaks up with his human girlfriend, Sophie Timmins. He will pursue an advanced degree in Tactical Strategies and Weaponry, and will be posted to Deep Space Three.
source: Pathways - VOY Ch 14; War Dragons - CT 1

info: Kirk receives a summons from the Planetary Court of Iotia to answer charges of breach of contract.
Framing story.
source: Day Of Honor: Treaty's Law - TOS

info: Main story. Sulu promoted to Captain.
Main story.
Sulu is given command of the Excelsior. Chekov is temporarily assigned First Officer. Janice Rand is Communications Officer.

Six crewmen from the Excelsior are taken hostage by the Anjiri-Nykuss, including Commander Chekov. The intervention of Captain Koloth nearly results in a war. Afterward, Chekov returns to the Enterprise as Security Chief.
At age 29, Tuvok is commissioned as an Ensign and is assigned to the Excelsior.
Main story.
Backstory.
Spock is killed by Commander Dellas at the Khitomer Conference. The timeline is corrected by Gary Seven. Spock is introduced to Romulan Senator Pardek.

As part of a recreational adventure, retired Admiral Korvak of the Romulan Star Empire arrives from the future and engages the Enterprise, causing an alternate timeline in which Kirk invents the Picard maneuver.
Due to post-traumatic stress from the Rura Penthe incident, Spock and McCoy begin to experience shadow memories from the joining of their minds years earlier.

The former pirate Ray Moss captures the USS Bill Of Rights in orbit around the planet Faramond using an alien dampening field. The Enterprise responds to the distress call, and gains a temporary reprieve from retirement.
Main story. Death of Amanda.
The Enterprise is ordered to transport a group of mediators to the violent planet Ssan. McCoy's ex-wife Jocelyn Treadway is killed.
The Enterprise-A finally returns to spacedock to be decommissioned, and the crew goes their separate ways.

T'Lar of Vulcan agrees to bond Spock's seven year-old niece (?) to Hasmek of Romulus, in an effort to further peace negotiations and obtain backing of the Vulcan Science Academy for a study of reunification.

Kirk, Scott and Chekov accept an invitation from Kirk's nephews, Alex and Julius, to assist in the founding of a colony world, Sanctuary. The colonists are taken hostage by the Falorians, who plan to invade their sister world, Huan, using Federation technology acquired from the Orion Syndicate. Spock, McCoy and Uhura arrive aboard the Klingon vessel K'Rator to assist Kirk, thus fulfilling the honor debt of Chancellor Azetbur of the Klingon High Council. Sulu and the Excelsior assist in the defense of Huan.
Kirk renews his relationship with Carol Marcus. The Enterprise-A is destroyed while defending the Excelsior from Klingon warships under the direction of Starfleet Chief Admiral Drake.

note: The date is given as Spring 2294, which would be after Kirk's disappearance in Generations.
info: Captain Sulu is captured by the Beta Promethean ship Sundew and is rescued by Kirk and crew aboard the star-yacht Plush Princess.
Chekov rejoins Captain Sulu's crew as First Officer aboard the Excelsior.

note: Both the stated year (2295) and Kirk's age (62) would be after Kirk's disappearance in Generations.
info: Kirk visits the Guardian of Forever for the final time.
Kal-Tor Lissan of the Falorians is murdered in his Federation prison cell by the Orion Syndicate.
The Romulans sign a non-aggression treaty with Triskelion.
Captains Kirk and Scott and Commander Chekov are honored during the launch of the Enterprise-B. Kirk is presumed dead when he disappears into the Nexus energy ribbon.
Guinan, along with Tolian Soran, are rescued from an El Aurian transport trapped in the Nexus.
Elaan of Troyius ruminates upon her time spent with Kirk years earlier.
Spock returns to Vulcan to act as than'tha for Saavik's orphaned student, Sanara.
source: The First Law Of Metaphysics - SNW 2

info: In the Small Magellanic Cloud, the Neyel cruiser Slicer follows the last known path of Tuskerslayer through the interspatial rift, emerging in Tholian space.
Demora Sulu, assigned as Helmsman aboard the Enterprise-B, is purportedly killed by Captain Harriman in an act of self-defense.
'About a year' after Kirk's disappearance.
As the mouth of the intergalactic rift drifts closer to Oghen, Tholian vessels begin to threaten the Neyel homeworld. Gran Drech'tor Zafir declares a genocidal war against the Tholians.
A 'holochamber' precursor to holodeck technology, is field-tested by Captain Harriman aboard the Enterprise.
By this time, Lt. M'Ress has vanished into a time portal and will emerge some 80 years later.
The Jenolen crashes while investigating a Dyson sphere. Captain Scott and Ensign Matt Franklin place themselves into stasis in a transporter buffer.
After completing mining operations on Janus 4, Engineer Vanderburg of the Federation gives a farewell speech to the Horta.

Unable to stem the continuing violent incursions of the Neyel, the Tholians request a meeting with the Federation to discuss a possible alliance. The Excelsior is sent into Tholian space to host the negotiations.

note: Flashback implies that Tuvok resigned immediately after TUC, while Pathways states that Tuvok completed just a three-year tour of duty aboard Excelsior before leaving Starfleet. This is six years after Tuvok's 'graduation', which we must assume refers to his advanced degree.
info: Tuvok resigns from Starfleet and returns to Vulcan, where he announces to his parents his decision to pursue the Kohlinar discipline.
Tuvok undergoes the Pon Farr and marries T'Pel.
Drs. Noonian Soong, Ira Graves and Emil Vaslovik discover an abandoned secret facility on Exo 3.
Birth of Jean-Luc Picard.
Lt. Arex falls through a wormhole while on a shuttle expedition and emerges 71 years later.
The Genesis Project is revived by Carol Marcus. She and Gillian Taylor are transported to the planet Pacifica aboard the USS Hermes, under command of Captain Uhura.
source: The Hero Of My Own Life - SNW 2

info: Thousands are killed in the Tomed incident between the Romulan Empire and the Federation.
source: TLE: Serpents Among The Ruins; Vulcan's Heart

info: Teska and Hasmek become the first recorded Vulcan/Romulan couple to be wed. The ceremony is attended by Spock, Sarek and Senator Pardek.
Katheryn Janeway's mother Gretchen, age six, learns that her father has been killed in the line of duty.
Tuvok's third son is born.
At age 53, Boothby begins his training to take over the gardening duties at Starfleet Academy from the previous caretaker, Aubrey.
Picard backstory.
Bajor is conquered by the Cardassian union.

The Cardassian survey vessel Sontok discovers the ruins of the lost Klingon colony Ch'gran on Raknal 5 near the Betreka Nebula. They refuse to yield the site to the Klingon vessel IKS Wo'bortas, touching off an 18-year cold war between the empires. Curzon Dax attempts to negotiate a settlement aboard the USS Carthage, whose crew includes Captain Vance Haden, Commander Rachel Garrett and Lt. Ian Troi. Enabran Tain is appointed head of the Obsidian Order.
source: TLE: The Art Of The Impossible Part 1

info: Lt. Edward Janeway meets Gretchen at a party celebrating the promotion of Gretchen's stepfather to Admiral.
Ambassador Spock and Commander Saavik are betrothed. The ceremony is attended by Lt. Picard and Admiral McCoy.
Six months after its launch under Captain Rachel Garrett, the Enterprise-C is attacked by a group of ships with a weapon similar to the Tholian web.

Under command of Captain Daithan Ruhalter, the USS Stargazer crosses the Galactic Barrier and is ambushed by an invading fleet of Nuyyad warships. Lt. Cmdr. Picard is forced to assume command following the deaths of the captain and executive officer.
Book

note: The Commander Rachel Garrett in this story must be a different person than the one in command of the Enterprise-C.
info: Book
Book
An accidental collision over Raknal 5 between a Cardassian freighter and a Klingon passenger ship causes increasing hostilities over the next few months.
source: TLE: The Art Of The Impossible Part 2

info: Picard meets Guinan for the first time (from his perspective) at Jeparly Station.
source: Together Again For The First Time - SNW 1

info: Book
Book
Book
Book
Four year-old Katheryn Janeway, daughter of Edward and Gretchen, learns her multiplication tables.

Encouraged by ongoing communication with Senator Pardek of Romulus, Ambassador Spock asks Solvar of the Vulcan Science Academy to commission a study on reunification with the Romulans. His request is deemed illogical.
Janeway visits Starfleet Academy and meets Cadet Data.
Spock's second request to the Vulcan Science Academy is similarly denied.
Backstory.
Captain Garrett of the Enterprise-C and Captain Kestrel of the Klingon vessel Qob'ral assist the Kolyati in repelling a Romulan invasion.
source: The Shoulders Of Giants - Two: Rayvis - SNW 5

info: A Klingon building on Raknal 5 is sabotaged by Romulans. While investigating, Lt. Cmdrs. Elian Vaughn and Ian Troi are trapped in the collapsing structure. Ian Troi dies from his injuries.
source: TLE: The Art Of The Impossible Part 3 Ch 19-26

info: Tuvok makes a pilgrimage to Mount Seleya, and ultimately decides to return to Starfleet.

note: The story features T'Pau of Vulcan, but it is unclear if this is the same T'Pau that purportedly died in Spock's World.
info: At the request of Romulan Commander Charvanek, Spock secretly travels to Vulcan to uncover Praetor Dralath's plans for war. Starfleet sends Commander Saavik of the USS Armstrong and Captain Picard of the USS Stargazer to extricate him. Spock's cover is threatened by the onset of Pon Farr. After departing Romulus, Saavik is rescued by the Enterprise-C. Upon return to Vulcan, Spock and Saavik are married. Captain Uhura is head of Starfleet Security.

The Enterprise-C is destroyed by Romulans while defending a Klingon outpost on Norenda 3. Richard Castillo survives in a lifepod. Tasha Yar, having traveled back in time from an alternate future, is captured alive by the Romulans. She will later give birth to a half-Romulan daughter, Sela.
source: The Fourth Toast - SNW 3; TLE: The Art Of The Impossible Part 3 Ch 27-29

info: Picard visits the Gorn homeworld and negotiates a peace settlement which lasts 25 years. Jack Crusher is science officer aboard the Stargazer.
Morgan 'Primus' Lefler determines that her four month-old daughter Robin has not inherited her immortality.
source: Alice, On The Edge Of Night - No Limits - NF

info: Mogh and Kaasin, the parents of six year-old Worf, are killed during a Romulan attack upon a Klingon research facility on Khitomer. Worf is adopted by Sergey and Helena Rozhenko. K'mpec becomes Chancellor of the Klingon Empire and cedes Raknal 5 to Cardassia.
source: TLE: The Art Of The Impossible Part 3 Ch 30-40

info: Janeway, captain of the Meadows tennis team, loses a decisive match to Shalarik of the Academy Institute.
Seven year-old Ro Laren witnesses the death of her father at the hands of Cardassians.
On Bajor, the Cardassians destroy a dam to submerge an excavation site containing a Tear of the Prophets. Glin Dukat escapes to higher ground.
Janeway, age 14, saves Hobbes Johnson from drowning on Mars.
Calhoun backstory.

note: Said to be twenty years prior to the main story; however, Si Cwan's age (eight) demands placement here.
info: Si Cwan backstory.
Elim Garak reaches the age of emergence and is placed for training at the Bamarren Institute on Cardassia.
source: A Stitch In Time Part 1 - DS9 27

info: Book
source: Double Helix 6: The First Virtue - TNG 56

info: August. During a visit to Central America on Earth, 15 year-old Chakotay announces his intention to leave his tribe and join Starfleet.
August. 15 month-old Harry Kim climbs out of his crib.
Janeway and Cheb Packer sneak into Magruder Mansion in Southern Ohio.
Janeway is accepted into Starfleet Academy. She discovers a chordate fossil on Mars.
Elim Garak is assigned as a junior probationist within the Obsidian Order.
source: A Stitch In Time Part 2 - DS9 27

info: Chakotay is transported to Starfleet Academy by Captain Hiromi Sulu, grandson of Hikaru.
Tasha Yar leaves Turkana 4 at age fifteen.
Chakotay returns home to Trebus to embark on a vision quest. He decides to return to the Academy.
Jadzia's sister Ziranne narrowly escapes injury while playing in the snow.

note: The dates given for the journal entries are almost entirely inaccurate, and are included here for reference only.
info: Magnus, Erin and Annika Hansen depart aboard the USS Raven on a secret mission to the Delta quadrant. Magnus's sister Irene writes in her journal.
The parents of Anika Hansen receive a communication through a temporal anomaly, urging them not to venture into Borg space.
M'k'n'zy backstory.
Backstory.
On Pelios Station, Ensign Benjamin Sisko assists Curzon Dax with diplomatic negotiations between the Bactricans, the Azziz, and the Federation.
source: The Music Between The Notes - The Lives Of Dax

info: Irene Hansen receives a transmission from Lt. Byron Morgan, informing her that Starfleet has lost contact with the Raven.
Seven year-old Robin Lefler lives on Tantalus while her father does plasma studies.
source: Lefler's Logs - Stardate 31345.3-31610.7, No Limits - NF

info: 12 year-old Neelix repairs an ancient energy weapon.
On Xenex, 20 year-old M'k'n'zy fulfills his obligation to sire a child for his brother's wife, Catrine.
Catrine is bonded in a 'land marriage' to the planet Xenex, blocking attempts to marry her into the G'lyndr clan.
source: A Lady Of Xenex - No Limits - NF

info: The staff of the Federation embassy at PojjanPiraKot, including Ambassador Spock, is evacuated due to an uprising among the population.
Janeway turns down a date with Will Riker to work on her junior honors thesis proposal for Admiral Owen Paris.
June. Part 1
June. B'Elanna Torres's father leaves her mother.
June. Riker begins dating Janice Eardman.
June. Robin Lefler completes a year spent on Rimbor with her parents, during which her mother begins to leave for weeks at a time.
source: Lefler's Logs - Stardate 32854.6, No Limits - NF

info: February. Book.
February. Starfleet concludes that the USS Raven and its crew are irrecoverable.
February. Chakotay graduates from the Academy with honors.
February. Robin Lefler and her parents return to Earth and take a camping trip on the Jersey shore.
source: Lefler's Logs - Stardate 33678.2, No Limits - NF

info: February. Ensign Janeway is assigned as Junior Science Officer aboard the USS Icarus under Admiral Paris. Six months into the mission, Janeway and Paris are captured by Cardassians and rescued by Lt. Justin Tighe.
February. Harry Kim begins playing the clarinet.
February. 16 year-old Si Cwan is forced by his father to prove his worthiness as a fighter by killing a wounded prisoner.
March. Book.
March. Neelix is given a hovercraft at the Feast of the First Night.
March. Tasha's later years at Starfleet Academy.

note: March. This is chronicled in detail in the Young Adult series of novels.
info: Worf and Zak Kebron room together at Starfleet Academy.
Ensign Eric Stiles is honored for his actions in saving the embassy staff four years earlier. Spock and McCoy accompany him to the ceremony.

Under direction of Commander Shelby, Picard and Dr. Crusher embark on the Monitor to Starbase 804 with orders to retrieve a Borg vessel. On Veridian 3, Kirk's body is retrieved by Romulans who revive him using technology acquired in an alliance with the Borg. The Farragut is destroyed. With orders to kill Picard, Kirk tracks down Worf on Qo'noS as well as Data and LaForge on Trilex before being apprehended on DS9. Later aboard the Challenger, Drs. Bashir and McCoy succeed in removing the Borg implants, while Picard, Crusher and Ambassador Spock are taken aboard after escaping from Borg captivity. The Monitor is fitted with a Borg transwarp engine and temporarily designated Enterprise, and travels to the Borg homeworld where V'Ger was repaired over a century earlier. Kirk sacrifices himself to destroy the Borg Central Node.

The crew of the USS Aldebaran and Tiris Jast aboard the Defiant are killed in a sneak attack upon Deep Space Nine by three Dominion ships. A Jem'Hadar named Kitana'klan is discovered on the station who claims to have been sent by Odo. After being told of a prophecy by Bajoran Istani Reyla, Jake Sisko enters the wormhole in search of his father. The prophecy also states that the son of Ben Sisko will be the Avatar and 10,000 people will die before his birth.

The Enterprise arrives at DS9 from the Badlands, bringing the lost Orb of Memory, as well as Commander Elias Vaughn who will become XO of DS9. Kira uploads Istani's prophetic book to Bajor's communications network and is attainted by the Vedek Assembly for her actions. Kitana'klan sabotages DS9's fusion reactor, but Kira jettisons the reactor prior to explosion. A second Jem'Hadar, Taran'atar, is revealed to be the true representative sent by Odo.

info: Eight year-old Miral Paris stows away aboard the Delta Flyer while Tom and Neelix conduct an away mission, and is stuck by a poisonous barb.

In an alternate future, the Voyager returns home after journeying for 23 years through the Delta and Beta quadrants. Over the next ten years, Chakotay will die, Kim will become Captain of the USS Rhode Island, Torres will be appointed Federation Liason to the Klingon Empire, Paris will begin writing holonovels, Tuvok will succumb to a degenerative brain disease, and Janeway will be promoted to Admiral.

info: August 9. Book.

Alternate future.
~2425. Tarina tells her grandchildren of her experience with the 'star people' of Voyager.
Melanie, an aspiring young writer, visits Jake Sisko at his home.
Captain Edward Sherwood of the Enterprise reports to Fleet Admiral Ian Kyle Riker that they have successfully repelled a Romulan invasion of the Guardian planet, now known as the Rock of Ages.
The Horta agree to relocate from Janus 4 to the Rock of Ages to help defend the Guardian of Forever against any future incursions.
President Toval Mot Than speaks at the launch of Kolya's first space exploration vessel, christened Enterprise.

info: Three Romulan Tal Shiar agents attempt to detonate the Bajoran Orb of Time inside the Guardian of Forever, but are killed by the Horta before completing their mission.
By this time, Vulcan-Romulan unification has occurred, Starfleet has rescinded General Order 7 on Talos 4, and the Temporal Integrity Commission has been established.
November 30. The Temporal Integrity Commission completes repairs to the timeline necessitated by the Enterprise's abduction of John Christopher in 1969.
The Voyager EMH backup module begins recording logs in the 27th year of his journey back to Federation space.
~3000. Alternate future.

~3100. Dax's host is killed during a shipboard accident in the Delta Quadrant. As the ship returns through the wormhole, Sisko and the Prophets arrange to have the ship emerge near Trill, allowing the Dax symbiont to be saved. The Federation is at peace with the Borg Cooperative.
All sentient biological lifeforms have been eradicated by Lore and the Children of Soong. Data will travel to the past to eliminate this timeline.
Several Horta decide to defect from the herd and leave the Rock of Ages with the Crystalline Entity.
The Borg attempt to assimilate the Guardian of Forever but are destroyed by the Horta.
After the humans have withdrawn their research installations from the Rock of Ages, Q begins to regularly visit the Guardian.
The evil entity Armus attempts to use the Guardian of Forever to seek revenge upon the Titans of Vagra 2 but is defeated by the Horta.
Odo visits the Guardian of Forever and asks to review the life of Kira Nerys.
A Federation memorial service is held on the Rock of Ages for the Elasians and Troyians, who had ultimately succeeded in destroying each other.
Humans evolve beyond their corporeal forms and join the Q in the Continuum.
The male Horta on the Rock of Ages answer the mating call of the lone female.
Tetsua, the 'honored last' of the Horta, finally witnesses the birth of her next generation.
source: Tears For Eternity - SNW 4; Guardians - SNW 7

info: The holographic crew of the UberEnterprise returns from a million-year mission of extragalactic exploration, and discovers that all sentient life in the Milky Way has evolved into a noncorporeal 'convergence'.
